wikipedia_page.main: Jack E. Cox, BSC, known variously as J. J. Cox, Jack Cox, John J. Cox and John Cox, was an English cinematographer born in London, on 26 July 1896. After a prolific career of 85 films in 33 years, Cox died in Surrey on 29 July 1960.

response: *Jack E. Cox (1896–1960), or John J. Cox, an English cinematographer
